## Setup Steps

### Step 1: Download ML Libraries

Run the download script to fetch Transformers.js and ONNX Runtime:

```bash
cd extension
chmod +x download-ml-libs.sh
./download-ml-libs.sh
```

This will:
- Download Transformers.js (~200KB)
- Download ONNX Runtime WASM files (~2MB)
- Create the necessary directory structure

**Expected output:**
```
🤖 Downloading ML Libraries for Local Presidio Extension
==========================================================

📁 Creating directory structure...
✓ Directories created

📦 Downloading Transformers.js library...
✓ Transformers.js downloaded (189K)

📦 Downloading ONNX Runtime WASM files...
✓ ONNX Runtime files downloaded

📊 Total library size: 2.2M

✅ Download complete!
```

### Step 2: Verify Files

Check that the files were downloaded:

```bash
ls -lh extension/libs/transformers/
ls -lh extension/libs/onnx/
```

You should see:
```
libs/
├── transformers/
│   └── transformers.min.js  (~200KB)
├── onnx/
│   ├── ort-wasm.wasm
│   ├── ort-wasm-simd.wasm
│   ├── ort-wasm-threaded.wasm
│   └── ort-wasm-simd-threaded.wasm
└── VERSION.txt
```

### Step 3: Reload Extension

1. Go to `chrome://extensions/`
2. Find "Local Presidio - PII Detector"
3. Click the **reload icon** 🔄

### Step 4: Load the ML Model

1. Click the extension icon in Chrome toolbar
2. Click **"Preload ML Model (Optional)"**
3. Wait for the model to download (~50MB, takes 30-60 seconds first time)

**Progress messages:**
```
Loading Transformers.js library...
↓
Initializing NER pipeline...
↓
Downloading NER model (~50MB, first time only)...
↓
✓ Model loaded successfully! NER detection enabled.
```

### Step 5: Test ML Detection

Upload a test file with names and organizations:

```txt
John Smith works at Acme Corporation in Singapore.
Contact: john.smith@acme.com or +65 91234567
```

**Expected detections:**
- ✅ **PERSON**: "John Smith" (NER detection, ~92% confidence)
- ✅ **ORGANIZATION**: "Acme Corporation" (NER detection, ~95% confidence)
- ✅ **LOCATION**: "Singapore" (NER detection, ~98% confidence)
- ✅ **EMAIL**: "john.smith@acme.com" (Regex detection, 100% confidence)
- ✅ **PHONE_SG**: "+65 91234567" (Regex detection, 100% confidence)

